      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Vinylcyclopropane reacts with HBr to yield a rearranged alkyl bromide. Follow the flow of electrons as represented by the curved arrows, show the structure of the carbocation intermediate in brackets, and show the structure of the final product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaElTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--bca6affa142b73591cc587a62ce493bd71683398/OChem_07_EC_034.jpg\" alt=\"A 2-step reaction shows vinylcyclopropane reacting with hydrogen bromide via abstraction of hydrogen and alkyl shift. The intermediate and products are unknown.\">",
